ŗln Memory Of Our Lovely Dad Robert John Price
23rd April 1942 - 28th March 2005 and
Ann-Marie Kimber
6th October 1956 - 6th October 2001"æ
ÄFor E. Clay Ulen, Jr.,
Who loved London and cherished this garden
and square above all others.
From his children, Tom, Sally, and Elizabeth"Æ
ÅTo my George
May the world's smallest violin play the blues just for you!
In our park, in our dreams, in our life.
Never another you, Maraki"ō
ÉTo my husband Stephen, the other half of me.
My love for you is beyond compare
 and I thank you for our life in Mayfair.
Yours forever, Nancy"¢
ōTo Elton M. Hyder Jr, my father, who first brought me to London,
and for Lewis P. Grinnan Jr., a dear friend, who allowed me to appreciate London."Ö
